	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Looking for good PC sync software</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />This is pretty much the only technical forum I frequent, so I figure I'll ask here.<br /><br />I'm looking for a piece of sync software that might do some or most of the following (in order of importance).<br />1. Sync automatically. I open a file, make a change and save. Open it on the other computer and the change is there without me having to click a &quot;re-sync&quot; button or anything.<br />2. Preserve date created, and date modified. This seems to be a tall order, since even copying files directly to/from a removable drive seems to destroy dates created.<br />3. Be relatively easy to add new folders to sync. Allow me to sync folders of an unlimited size.<br />4. It should be easy to set up in the first place, but I'm definitely not adverse to a super complicated but one time setup.<br />5. Free software is cool, but not free is good too if it does everything else.<br /><br />For those familiar, I'm looking for something like <a href="https://www.dropbox.com/" class="postlink">Dropbox</a> except that I would like dates created preserved, and I do not care about &quot;the cloud&quot; benefit and the space limitations that come with it. Ideally it would work through just the home network. I ask here because there are over 9,000 sync programs. I'm hoping that someone here already happens to use one that does these things that they are happy with, otherwise I guess I really will just have to try them all.<br /><br />Edit: I guess I should mention both computers are Windows, and I don't care about cross platform compatibility at all.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
