	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Tepples: I guess you're looking for me to word things differently? <br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">To make this work, you would need to run this software on a server with unlimited storage space.<br /></div><br />I mean that the software/service should not limit how much I'm syncing (like Dropbox only allows me 2 GB, at least for free). I will obviously be limited by the harddrive space of the computers involved.<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">How would each computer find the other computers with syncable folders, especially as these computers' IP addresses change? </div><br />The hope is that the software will figure that out, as dropbox does, or software like <a href="http://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=35460" class="postlink">Mouse without borders</a> does. <br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Or does your &quot;super complicated but one time setup&quot; include installing DHCP reservations through the router appliance's administration interface?</div><br />It probably doesn't include that, because I am rather clueless about networking things in general. If my lack of knowledge in that area is keeping me from doing this, I'm certainly open to learning.

		

